<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-03T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="922" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d922">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/1147: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-03T16:00:00-04:00">July 3, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>220. Your 380, June 30, 5 p.m. The Department is making a study of the
                            taxation questions raised in your telegram under reference, but, <pb facs="1105" n="995" xml:id="pg_995"/> pending the issuance of
                            further instructions, your proposed reply to Foochow quoted in paragraph
                            1 of your telegram is approved.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>